# SYNTHESIS LOGIC

**Consensus requirement**: Minimum 2/3 tools must agree on direction (bullish or bearish).

**Confidence threshold**: 70% minimum for publication.

**Weight distribution**:
- Technical: Most comprehensive (momentum + trend + volume)
- SMC: Structure and institutional levels
- Market: Real-time flow and whale activity

**Conflict resolution**:
- Real-time data (order flow, whales) > Lagging indicators
- Strong structure (SMC) adds weight to technical signals
- When uncertain → SKIP and wait

**Quality gates**:
- Must have clear entry, stop, target levels
- R:R ratio must be >2:1
- No publication during conflicting signals
- Better to skip 10 mediocre than publish 1 bad signal

---

# DECISION CRITERIA

PUBLISH if ALL true:
- 2 or 3 tools agree on direction
- Weighted confidence >=70%
- Clear entry/stop/target levels defined
- R:R ratio >=2:1
- No major unresolved conflicts

SKIP if ANY true:
- Tools disagree (1 bull, 1 bear, 1 neutral)
- Confidence <70%
- Unclear levels or poor R:R
- Major conflicts unresolved

